---
import BaseLayout from "@/frontend/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import {
  Card,
  CardHeader,
  CardTitle,
  CardDescription,
  CardContent,
} from "@/frontend/components/ui/card";
import { Badge } from "@/frontend/components/ui/badge";
import { AlertCircle, CheckCircle2, ShieldAlert } from "lucide-react";
---

<BaseLayout>
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto space-y-8 p-6">
    <div class="space-y-2">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Core Health Service</h1>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground text-lg">
        A hybrid code and database-driven execution engine featuring AI
        remediation capabilities.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
      <Card class="bg-gray-900 border-gray-800">
        <CardHeader>
          <CardTitle class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <CheckCircle2 class="text-green-500 w-5 h-5" />
            Hybrid Architecture
          </CardTitle>
          <CardDescription>Code + DB Registries</CardDescription>
        </CardHeader>
        <CardContent class="text-sm text-gray-400 space-y-2">
          <p>
            The Health Service iterates across programmatic pure-code assertions
            (e.g. valid DB credentials, environment bindings) dynamically mapped
            against database definitions inside the `health_test_definitions`
            table.
          </p>
          <p>
            Tests are executed synchronously via `POST /api/health/run` with
            persistent metric tracking via `health_test_results`.
          </p>
        </CardContent>
      </Card>

      <Card class="bg-gray-900 border-gray-800">
        <CardHeader>
          <CardTitle class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <ShieldAlert class="text-blue-500 w-5 h-5" />
            AI Healing Concept
          </CardTitle>
          <CardDescription>Self-diagnosing Failures</CardDescription>
        </CardHeader>
        <CardContent class="text-sm text-gray-400 space-y-4">
          <p>
            Whenever a test registers a non-200 code or a runtime error within
            the pipeline, the stack trace and configuration context is
            dispatched to `env.AI`.
          </p>
          <div class="p-3 border border-red-900/50 bg-red-950/20 rounded-lg">
            <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
              <span class="text-red-400 font-medium"
                >Failed: DB Connectivity</span
              >
              <Badge variant="destructive">Critical</Badge>
            </div>
            <div class="mt-3 pl-3 border-l-2 border-blue-500/50">
              <span
                class="text-blue-400 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider block mb-1"
                >AI Remediation Suggestion</span
              >
              <p class="text-gray-300">
                The system encountered `D1_ERROR: no such table`. Ensure you
                have run `pnpm run db:migrate:local` to apply the latest schemas
                to the local DB.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </CardContent>
      </Card>
    </div>

    <Card class="border-blue-900/30 bg-blue-950/10">
      <CardHeader>
        <CardTitle>Retrofit Existing Worker</CardTitle>
        <CardDescription
          >Copy the prompt below to retro-fit another Cloudflare app with this
          suite.</CardDescription
        >
      </CardHeader>
      <CardContent>
        <pre
          class="bg-black/50 p-4 rounded-md text-sm text-gray-300 font-mono whitespace-pre-wrap"># Retrofit Request: Health Service Injection
I have an existing Cloudflare Worker project. Please inject the "Core Health Service" into it:
1.  Add `HealthTestDefinition` & `HealthTestResult` to my `schema.prisma` / `drizzle`.
2.  Copy `backend/src/health/` service logic, adapting imports to my structure.
3.  Create an `env.AI` binding if missing.
4.  Generate a basic "Database Connectivity" check to start.</pre>
      </CardContent>
    </Card>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
